article.headline: Vermont 73, Cornell 60
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Cornell outscored Vermont in the second half, but a dismal first-half doomed the Big Red and gave the Catamounts a 73-60 victory at Patrick Gymnasium on Friday. Cornell was able to put just 14 points on the board in the first half while Vermont scored 33. The second half turned around for Cornell, when it scored 46. But Vermont's 40 was more than enough to keep the Catamounts in the game. Taylor Coppenrath's 27 points and nine rebounds led Vermont. T.J. Sorrentine added 17 points and 10 assists. For Cornell, Ka'Ron Barnes led with 23 points. Eric Taylor grabbed eight rebounds while contributing 5 points. Cornell was done in by its shooting, hitting just 23 percent of the baskets it attempted in the first half before turning it around to score 51 percent of the times it attempted in the second half. The Big Red was even worse attempting three-pointers, hitting none of their 13 first-half attempts. The victory was Vermont's first in five games. Cornell is 2-3.
